T3 (Fig. 
7E
) a cleaning limb. Protopodite with two long setae (dp and d2) and one shorter seta (d1). First endopodal segment with short subapical e-seta. Second and third endopodal segments fused, with short f-seta not reaching tip of segment. Terminal part (fusion between distal part of third and fourth segment) a pincer organ, bearing a medium length seta (h3), a short serrated seta (h2), and a very short seta (h1), length of seta h3 ~ 2/3 that of fused segment, seta h2 ~ 1/2 length of seta h3.

CR (Fig. 
7F
). Reduced, with elongated, triangular base; distally with long flagellum-like seta and subapically with a short seta.
